which depends on the function parameter emsg and is therefore not inherently invariant. The #ifdef/#else preprocessor conditional is not a C runtime controlling expression covered by this rule. All other statements are simple assignments and a function call, not controlling expressions, so there are no fragments that require investigation for Rule 14.3.
